    <string name="section_tutorial_title">üìñ Instructions and Tips</string>

    <string name="section_tutorial_item1">1. Fast scrolling is supported: swipe right-to-left and up or down. Quick navigation to the start or end of the file is available by tapping the top or bottom right corner.</string>

    <string name="section_tutorial_item2">2. Fast copying is supported: long-press anywhere and use the "ALL" button. Quick text deletion is also available via "ALL" + "DELETE" on the keyboard.</string>

    <string name="section_tutorial_item3">3. Editing very large files may be resource-intensive depending on the device. For most scenarios (up to 100,000 characters or more) the editor performs normally.</string>

    <string name="section_tutorial_item4">4. After changing syntax highlighting settings, it is recommended to restart the application.</string>

    <string name="section_tutorial_item5">5. Data protection is implemented using AES-GCM with HMAC-SHA256 and PBKDF2 (75,000 iterations). Use a random and sufficiently complex password for strong protection. Note: a weak password undermines cryptographic measures; for sensitive data use a password manager.</string>

    <string name="section_tutorial_item6">6. This editor is part of the Syndes ecosystem. Use for work tasks is permitted and not restricted by the license. The project is free and distributed as open source.</string>

    <string name="section_tutorial_item7">7. Disclaimer: the developers are not responsible for consequences of using the editor. We strive to provide reliable software, but complete stability cannot be guaranteed. Regular backups reduce the risk of data loss.</string>

